cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper focuses on deep convolutional neural networks and their features, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of deep models, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper analyzes the resiliency of deep features, which is related to the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of perturbations to measure the effect on the final score suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses compression rates, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
